name: Seattle Aquarium
directions: Hidden by the otters, outside! there are gendered bathrooms inside, but gender neutral ones just past the otter tanks outside.
comment: You have to pay to get into the aquarium, so this is really just useful for folks that were going to visit the aquarium and were worried about bathrooms there

name: Roy St. Coffee & Tea
directions: In the back of the cafe, to the left of the cash register and down the hallway
comment: I walked in without buying anything, so I assume it is open to the public

name: Cincinnati Zoo
directions: At the front entrance and in several other places (see park map), single stall, family restrooms are available for visitors to the park.
comment: I have never had a problem here.

name: Om Cafe
directions: Back of store, to right of counter
comment: There are two, single-stall, unisex bathrooms for customers and people attending events.

name: Sidewinder Coffee
comment: Restrooms are labelled "Men" and "Women", but this coffee shop has a large transgender and gender queer clientele and employees.

name: True Coffe
directions: Back of store to the right

name: \aut\ BAR
directions: one downstairs in back, one at top of stairs
comment: Ann Arbor's LGBT bar. single-stall non-gendered bathrooms.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: two gender neutral, single stall bathrooms in the very back right of the store

name: Chicago Diner
directions: back of restaurant
comment: the bathrooms are gender labeled but both single stall and the staff will always inform you that you can use either one while waiting.  gendered signs will eventually get taken down once new signs are designed!

name: Reed College
directions: Bottom floor of the Gray Campus Center

name: University of Florida - Peabody Hall
directions: third floor of Peabody Hall
comment: office space is open Mon-Fri 8am-5pm

name: Evergreen State College Campus Activities Building
directions: On the top floor next to the Flaming Eggplant.

name: Evergreen State College Housing Community Center
directions: Next to laundry room.

name: Pride Centre of Edmonton
comment: Wheelchair access to the building itself is at the back door, which is often locked, so you might have to ring the doorbell.

name: The Bus Stop Theatre
directions: All three bathrooms are gender neutral!
comment: Bathrooms are always available when the bar/theatre is open. Depending on the event, there may be cover to enter the establishment.

name: French Meadow Bakery & Cafe
comment: Restrooms are explicitly trans-friendly.

name: Mugby Junction
directions: When you go straight through the entrance, move to the back left of the lounge area.  There are two unisex single-stall bathrooms.
comment: Bathrooms are public, just go on in and use them--they're explicitly trans-friendly.

name: Starbucks
directions: Back of the store
comment: To my knowledge, you don't have to be a paying customer.

name: Adele H. Stamp Student Union
directions: On the basement level, near the TerpZone.

name: Maguire Hall, Georgetown University
directions: 2nd Floor, to the left of the elevator. There are two. One is accessable.

name: Herrick Library
directions: On the ground floor there are two single-occupancy gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Moravian College
directions: First, second, and third floors; east side of building
comment: Students, faculty, staff, college visitors

name: Rainbow Youth
directions: Open 11-5 Monday to Friday, and when meetings/events etc are on outside of those hours!

name: Ashland Food Co-op
directions: Back center of store, no bags inside

name: Kroger's
directions: Upfront, one large bathroom, is a "family" bathroom, between the Women's and Men's. Has a toilet, urinal and changing station inside.
comment: Not sure if you have to be paying customer, usually large grocery or department stores don't pay that much attention.

name: Village Books
directions: Little room behind the front counter.

name: Taqueria La Tapatia
directions: Right end of counter and back

name: Royal Cafe
directions: Dual unisex single stalls down hall to right.

name: Promise Natural Foods & Bakery
directions: Single stall in back left of store.
comment: Colorful ambience

name: Berryvale
directions: In the hallway in back of the cafe.

name: target
directions: By the pharmacy

name: UC Santa Cruz Quarry
directions: Up the stairs to the bike coop.

name: Starbucks Roxborough
directions: Near the front entrance on Ridge Ave. Two single occupant restrooms recently converted to gender neutral!

name: Phoenix Coffee
directions: On the side of the shop opposite the street.
comment: The baristas there are some of the sweetest people you'll meet, I'd honestly be shocked if they told you off for using the bathroom without buying something. They won't care. They do make awesome coffee though.

name: Carolyn Tanner Irish Humanities Building
directions: Take the elevator or the stairs up to the 4th floor. There are two single-stall bathrooms located down the hall just past the Philosophy Department office.
comment: The building is open to the public from 7 am to 5 pm. Students and faculty are in and out all day, so don't worry about just going upstairs and using the bathroom.

name: Grotto Pizza
directions: Between the men's room and ladies' room.
comment: Probably have to be a paying customer.

name: Upper Cup Cafe
comment: Local community coffee shop. Really nice African guys who are the owners. Great Chai & nice artwork displays

name: Cafe Madeline
comment: They won't kick up a fuss if you don't buy anything but it would probably be helpful to try to buy something

name: NYU Bookstore
directions: At the back of the in-store ThinkCoffee which is on the left of the store.
comment: You don't need to be a paying customer or have an NYU id to gain access

name: Miss Florence Diner
directions: Go in the side door by J R's pub and grill and head straight. They are gendered but single stalls.
comment: If you follow the instructions, no one will even know.

name: The Roost
directions: It's across from the counter type seating and between the stairs and the place where you get water. It's cute. They're labeled 1 and 2.
comment: If you come in the door on the corner and head straight  up the stairs (it will be on the left), no one will care.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In the back next to the sample area
comment: two single, ungendered restrooms with yummy smelling soaps and lotions. I'm pretty sure it's accessible, too, but I'll double check next time I'm in.

name: big daddys
directions: in the back of the bar
comment: entirely safe space

name: Charmington's
directions: Walk to the other side of the coffee shop, make a left and it's on your left just past the entrance to the kitchen.
comment: The coffee shop is built into an apartment complex. People stay for coffee, but sometimes people pass through. No one would bat an eyelash if you just went in to use the bathroom. But they're also an awesome coffee shop, so consider supporting them, while you're there!

name: Apple Store
comment: Open to everyone.

name: UCF Pride Commons
directions: It's in the UCF Campus across from Marketplace. The closest parking lots are the Libra Community Parking Lot or Garage B next to the Recreation and Wellness Center (Gym).

name: Newtown Community & Cultural Centre
street: corner of Rintoul and Colunbo St
directions: down corridor to the left
comment: public bathroom - usually only open between 9am and 3p during the week

name: UCF Smoothie King
street: UCF, Student Union, Pegasus Circle, Bldg 52
directions: Connected to the Student Union building is the Smoothie King, it's not directly inside the Union.
comment: You can most likely just walk in to use the bathroom I don't believe you have to be a paying customer.

name: Holston Valley Unitarian Universalist Church
directions: all restrooms are gender neutral. One restroom in the hallway to the church kitchen and both restrooms in the RE building are accessible.

name: The Root Cellar Organic Cafe & Bakery
directions: Back of cafe, at the very end of the hallway around the wall.
comment: Just walking in is acceptable. Has a nice and welcoming staff. Bathrooms have chalkboards on the doors that usually say something humorous like "extra terrestrial" on them, have yet to encounter anything gendered.

name: Trade Gallery/ One Thoresby Street
directions: Ground floor toilets both cubicles & shared sink. Nice & rustic in a positive sense
comment: Bit out of the way so not the choice if you need a wee in town, but good to know, non?

name: Nottingham Contemporary
directions: Opposite cafe bar downstairs. Three bathrooms red doors
comment: purple ones outside performance space are gender specific so go through into cafe space opp bar

name: Bard Simon's at Simon's Rock
directions: Go through the Security Entrance and the single stall bathrooms are on the left.
comment: Act like a student. No key card is necessary.

name: Cardiff University Student's Union
directions:
Third floor turn left
Fourth floor turn right
comment: Do not need to be a student

name: Metro Queen St
directions: In the back, by NZ Natural Ice Cream and Pita Pit, behind the staircase leading out.
comment:
Marked for handicapped patrons, may encounter resistance if an abled person attempts to use it.

Note: would not recommend the mens in the same area for any trans folk, tends to be unclean and feels unsafe.

name: Esquires Lorne St
directions:
Entering via Queen St: next to Mrs Higgins cookies, up two flights of escalators, into Esquires, through a door in the back of the seated area immediately inside.
Entering via Lorne St: up the stairs, past the counter, turn right and the bathroom is through a door at the back of the seated area.
comment:
Technically a public bathroom, just happens to be attached to Esquires, so you are entirely free and entitled to use it.
Happens to be pretty secluded and safe, too.

name: Auburn University Student Center
directions: First Floor across from the CopyCat store

name: Ferguson Center
directions: 1st (bottom floor) near elevators.

name: Farrah Hall
directions: 1st (bottom floor) next to Room 120.
comment: Building doors locked on weekends.

name: The Dollar Tree
directions: In the back, to the left, near the frozen/refridgerator foods

name: Dairy Queen
directions: Off to the right when you enter.
comment: It's possible to slip in and out quickly.

name: Bellingham Flea Market
directions: It's at the top of a set or stairs, follow the pink line with arrows on it.
comment: This place is very chill, so it's easy to just slip in to use the restroom and out again. They are often short on toilet paper, but in that case there are almost always paper towels.

name: Daily Groceries
directions: In the back of the store on the left, walk through the curtains and straight ahead.

name: Cobalt
comment: The bathrooms are unisex but have some open stalls and more urinals than single bathrooms.

name: Deja Brew
directions: left of the counter

name: Raw Deal
directions: North side of first floor

name: Lehigh University Main Building
directions: Fourth floor; use back stairwells

name: San Diego LGBT Pride
directions: In the main hallway on your right.

name: UC San Diego
directions: Second floor of price center east, next to the nail salon

name: Kleinau Theatre
directions: Second floor of the Communications Building.
comment: These restrooms are gendered but set far enough back that they have served as a relative safe haven from the more regularly traversed restrooms in the same building.

name: Barnes and Noble Booksellers
directions: Back wall by the art books
comment: Act like you're paying. The restrooms are gender segregated. However, the staff have been overwhelmingly supportive and have posed no threat for using chosen/desired restroom

name: Prentice Hall KSU
directions: In the Prentice Hall lobby- accessible and gender-neutral bathroom.
comment: Lobby is open from 8am-2am Mon-Thurs, 8am-10pm Fri, 11am-10pm Sat, and 11am-2am Sun.

name: Donkey Coffee
directions: Both restrooms are gender neutral.

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: Two unisex single restrooms at the back of the restaurant.

name: Ninth Street Bakery
directions: On the right before you get to the main bakery door.
comment: You can use it without being a paying customer since they're outside the main bakery part of the building.

name: Brooklyn Park Library
directions: Down short hall beyond service desk
comment:
M-Th 9 am - 9 pm
F, Sat 9 am - 5 pm

name: Starbucks
directions: ask cashier for door number code.
comment: in theory it's only for paying customers, but 99% of the time we will give you the code if you just ask nicely for it.

name: UNH Dimond Library
directions: Beside the ATSC/IT Desk
comment: Not yet labeled, just go through the windowed door. Labels coming soon!

name: Philadelphia Chutney Company
directions: The place is pretty small so the bathrooms are hard to miss. They're down a short corridor next to the register.

name: Chipotle
directions: ground floor to left of cash register
comment: Sometimes may require you to be paying customer.

name: University of Minnesota, TC
directions: Fourth Floor
comment: Not single stall, but entire bathroom can be locked from inside.

name: UNIT1 Art Gallery
directions: It's the only door from the main gallery on the first floor.
comment: It's a work of art in itself, the "toilet time machine".

name: UNCA Ramsey Library
directions: Take elevator to 1st floor (very bottom),the unisex/accessable bathroom will be through the doors and directly in your left.

name: University of Wisconsin Whitewater
directions: Most general campus buildings now have unisex/gender neutral bathrooms, usually on the main or first floor of each building.

name: Dosa
comment: Two single-occupancy gender-neutral restrooms

name: Lucy in Disguise with Diamonds
directions: Straight ahead on the left, before the dressing room.
comment: There are two single restrooms, and they are gendered, but any employee will tell you they're meant to be neutral.  Most of the employees are LGBTQ.
